body:
@SilversterSunset if you are wishing to use with external CL, the --externalcl flag will need to be set, otherwise internal CL is used. In debug mode (not recommended for production) it would be expected to see peers not responding. 

If wishing to get rid of the external cl (prysm in your case), I can see that running without the flag (having previously run with it), the node does start to sync, but the internal CL has to catch up also, so the node may appear not to sync for a little while (couple of minutes).

The reason the logs are bloated is because a high % of peers are non-responding, which is possibly something to look at in future if we make improvements to sentinel.
